io.confluent.ksql.function.udaf

Interface Udaf<I,A,O>

  • Type Parameters:
    I - the input type
    A - the intermediate aggregate type
    O - the final output type
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    TableUdaf<I,A,O>

    public interface Udaf<I,A,O>
    Udaf represents a custom UDAF (User Defined Aggregate Function) that can be used to perform aggregations on KSQL Streams.

    Type support is presently limited to: int, Integer, long, Long, boolean, Boolean, double, Double, String, Map, and List.

    Sequence of calls is:

    1. initialize(): to get the initial value for the aggregate
    2. aggregate(value, aggregate): adds value to the aggregate.
    3. merge(agg1, agg2): merges to aggregates together, e.g. on session merges.
    4. map(agg): reduces the intermediate state to the final output type.
